            <abstract>
                <p><foreign xml:lang="gez">Qǝne</foreign> without type indication in the manuscript that mentions
                    a <foreign xml:lang="grc">logion</foreign>, i.e. the breastplate of the high priest. It has eight lines, meaning
                    that it might be classified as a <foreign xml:lang="gez">mawaddǝs qǝne</foreign> according to
                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:Guidi1900Qene"/></bibl>. 
                    It is attributed to <persName ref="PRS14574GabraLeul" cert="high" corresp="SD">Gabra Lǝʿul</persName> 
                    in the manuscript.</p>
            </abstract>
